============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Gini Coefficient
Category:   Statistics
Definition: Measures income inequality from 0 (equal) to 1 (one person has all)
Formula:    G = 1 - 2∫L(x)dx
Economist:  Corrado Gini
Example:    USA Gini ~0.41; Denmark ~0.29; South Africa ~0.63

Concept:    Elasticity
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Responsiveness of demand to price change
Formula:    PED = %dQd / %dP
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Gasoline demand inelastic; luxury goods elastic

Concept:    Supply and Demand
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Price determined where quantity supplied equals demanded
Formula:    P* where Qd=Qs
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Housing prices rise when population grows but supply stays fixed

